    <!-- Member 1 -->
    <div class="team-member" data-name="Bhagat Singh Rawat" data-designation="Founder & CEO" data-more="When we talk about the spirit of the Himalayas, one name that stands tall is Mr. Bhagat Singh Rawat, the founder of Himalayan Hikers. A man of grit, determination, and compassion, Mr. Rawat has dedicated his life not only to mountaineering but also to empowering people and protecting the fragile ecosystem of the Himalayas. His journey is not just about scaling mountains but about building opportunities, fostering responsibility, and inspiring thousands.

A trained mountaineer and former trainer at the Nehru Institute of Mountaineering (NIM), Uttarkashi, he has contributed immensely to the field of adventure. His expertise not only shaped many young mountaineers but also laid the foundation for his larger mission.

From being an employee to creating opportunities, Mr. Rawat built Himalayan Hikers into one of India’s leading trekking organisations. Through it, he generated employment for countless local youths, helping families achieve financial stability and making him a respected figure among the younger generation.

Deeply committed to the environment, he promoted responsible tourism — encouraging people to enjoy the mountains without polluting them. His eco-conscious approach ensures that trekking goes hand in hand with protecting the fragile Himalayan ecosystem.

Equally remarkable is his long service in disaster management, where he spent years helping people during natural calamities. His selfless dedication turned him into a symbol of hope and resilience in the region.

Today, Mr. Rawat is admired as much for his achievements as for his character. His journey — from doing a job to generating jobs, from climbing peaks to uplifting communities — continues to inspire trekkers, youth, and mountain lovers across Indiay.">
      <img src="img/team/Bhagat-Singh-rawat.jpeg" alt="Bhagat Singh Rawat">
      <h4>Bhagat Singh Rawat</h4>
      <p class="designation">Founder & CEO</p>
      <button class="read-more-btn">Read full story</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Member 2 -->
    <div class="team-member" data-name="Chain Singh Rawat" data-designation="Co-Founder & Partners" data-more="Mr. Chain Singh Rawat, Co-Founde Partners of Himalayan Hikers, is a distinguished mountaineer and community leader whose journey from a trekking guide to a respected figure in adventure tourism is truly inspiring. A former trainer at the prestigious Nehru Institute of Mountaineering (NIM), Uttarkashi, he has mentored countless mountaineers, instilling in them discipline, safety, and respect for the mountains.

Beyond mountaineering, he has played a vital role in natural disaster management, supporting families in times of crisis and personally training Himalayan villagers to face such challenges with resilience. His dedicated service has made him a respected name in the Rupin-Supin Valley of Uttarakhand, where he is known for always being ready to help.

Passionate about preserving culture and livelihoods, he has promoted local homestays, empowering families while offering trekkers an authentic cultural experience. Through Himalayan Hikers, he has created employment opportunities for youth, guided many to train at NIM, and inspired them to establish their own ventures—ensuring a chain of opportunities across the region.

With a deep commitment to eco-friendly and responsible tourism, he consistently advocates for keeping the Himalayas clean and unspoiled. His life’s work reflects that true mountaineering is not only about summiting peaks, but also about protecting nature, uplifting communities, and inspiring generations.

At Himalayan Hikers, we are proud to have his guidance in shaping trekking as a means of adventure, cultural exchange, and sustainable development..">
